Note: The color of the text shows the color of the dragon speaking if it isn't Merenth. Kaelia can't speak dragon but she iunderstands it. If it's more than one it's <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;">this color</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->.  If it's colored while Merenth is speaking, it refers to the color of the dragon she's talking about.<br>
<br>
IC:  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;But I'm not inside the village, am I?  I chose this spot because it disturbs people when I hunt.  The barrier doesn't reach this far at the moment.  I can feel that.  They'll come looking for me.  But you can still come and watch if you want.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth nods and her eyes cloud over again.  This time she doesn't bother to shake it off.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;I saved her the one time I was caught.  I don't know why they wanted her, she was barely the size of a small grass snake.  But that Dark lord knew about feather-dragons.  He was close to driving her insane because he took control over her.  He tried the same with me but my mind was too strong for him and it backfired.  So he tried to cast me off. Of course, it had to be after I watched him kill my parents.  My brother was under torture.  I just <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>knew</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> somehow that I became leader once they had died.  So when he tried to chain me down half of my clan just...died.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Kaelia takes off suddenly to flutter to Merenth's nose, shivering.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mistress, stop.  I don't want to remember.  It's not good for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to re-&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;The ones he managed to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>control</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> were the ones that dropped dead right away.  The irony there was that he had already cast an immortality spell on me because he thought he could do it.  And he had augmented my magic.  When he tried to take me over most of the remaining clan screamed and fell dead.  I sort of went crazy and blew up most of his fortress when I released all of my magic at once in a wild blast.  Most of the surviving dragons fled except Kaelia because she was stuck in a cage.  I was the only one left and I was too busy tearing his men to pieces.  At my age and in my state I was small, fast, and deadly with my claws and teeth.  Her tiny cage was so small her tail poked out and when I stepped on it she screeched.  I spotted her and stepped on the corner of the cage.  The thing broke apart and after I took care of the rest of the men trying to recapture me I noticed she was clinging to the end of my tail.  And that's just the short version.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Kaelia sinks her teeth into the queen's nose and makes Merenth finally snap out of her lethargy and stare at her claws that she was unconsciously scraping on the stone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*Gods.  It's like I was there again.  I can almost feel those knives again.  I would have snapped off his head when I found it out if it wasn't for him and his straps and chains.  It was because of the magic he gave me that I destroyed it all.  And all the blood.  My wings... I used the old way.  I flayed them with my own claws and splattered their brains all over the ground.  I can almost feel the energy each kill gave me, flowing...  I did it because I had to.  If I failed my dragons would die off.  I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>had</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to do it!*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth throws her head up, throwing Kaelia off and giving off a spout of bright blue flame into the sky.  She calls her sorrow to the clouds and three dragons appear out of nowhere in the distance, alerted.  They fly quickly in the direction of their queen.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Sorry.  It's just that I get caught up in it once I get started.  But my wings went from bright to dark in that one night.  Sometimes I still find bits of their skulls stuck in between my scales on my claws.  I can't forget.  Not until I get him back.  It's like how you can't forget what happened.  No member of my clan can forget.  I was the one who freed them all and saved their lives.  And now they live forever, with that memory burned into their minds with the pain they had to suffer.  I'm charged with purging it.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth looks skyward and spots the approaching dragons, and waves a wing at a lower, wider ledge for them to land on, where they couldn't see Kyla.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;I couldn't save my brother.  I know he's still there.  I can still feel his presence.  But it's tainted because of that mage.  I have to free him.  He's still suffering.  He looks to me as his leader but he can't come to me when I need him, and I can't go to him when he needs me.  I can hear him calling my name sometimes when it's quiet enough.  But I have to wait before I can go.  Too long.  Too long...&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The three dragons land with precision on the lower ledge and incline their head in salute to Merenth, spreading out their wings to display the varying shades of red.  One is green, one small and sky blue, one completely ruby-shaded.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;Queen Merenth, leader of the ruby wings.  We heard you call.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">&quot;What has made you call so?  We haven't heard such a tone from you for centuries.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Have you been remembering it again, Lady?&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Yes, I have.  Such memories resurface from time to time.  But I did not call you.  Why is it that you come to me?  Although I would like <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">Corathin</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> to come up here.  I have someone here I wish you to meet.  And only you.  <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Narta</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> and <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">Kitrin</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->, you may return to your interrupted doings if you have nothing to report.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;">&quot;I bring news, Lady. That demon is trying to steal eggs in the Oven again.  Our magic can't harm it-&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Then use your claws and shred it.  That's what they're for.  There isn't any need to come to me when you can deal with it yourself.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">&quot;The Dark one is coming back.  We found one of his Hunters chasing hatchlings again.  And where there is one...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;There are always more, unfortunately.  I'll call more mages over to your group later.  For now you should keep your little ones and your eggs in the dens and stay on your guard.  Keep your own mages on alert to flay any fool with Hunters' gear who happens to come near.  <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">Corathin</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->, you came with <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Narta</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->, didn't you?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I did, Mistress.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Good.  She can relay.  You come up here.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;">&quot;As you order, Queen Merenth.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The two dragons lower their heads in a farewell salute to their queen before dropping from their ledge and disappearing into thin air.  The sky blue one flies up to the higher ledge to sit next to Merenth's head and rubs his head on hers before looking around to see who she wanted him to meet.  He nearly falls off when he sees Kyla looking at him.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Lady, is this-&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;A half-dragon.  Like you.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
