<br>
&quot;Corathin!  I missed you!&quot;<br>
<br>
He only laughs and teases her with his tail  before turning back to the small gold smiling shyly at him.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Hello Kyla.  I'm Corathin.  I'd heard our queen had stumbled upon a village with half-dragons but I never thought she would want me here to meet one.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth opens one eye to look at the little blue before closing it again and smiling.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Always expect the unexpected from your queen.  I thought that was the first thing I taught you.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Of course, Lady. I just can't seem to figure out <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>when</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I should expect it.  And I certainly wasn't a member of your clan when you first found me.  And a good thing, too!&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;It was their fault for attacking a ruby-wing, half or not.  If you had been I would have torn them to pieces.  They were lucky.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I suppose you're right, but lightning isn't exactly a fun thing to get hit by when you're hungry.  I could almost feel sorry for them!&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Don't you have a young lady to talk to instead of bantering with me?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
He turns back to Kyla, grinning.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I'm sorry.  She found me when a small group of dragons was trying to eat me.  She kinda stunned them and adopted me.  I'm the only one in our clan who can tease her because any other one would end up in so much trouble he'd be rendered flameless for a month.  I'm the only one who knows her well enough.  She's like the mother I never had, really.  Since my real one died when I was really young.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I wanted you to come here to talk about half-dragons.  Not about your special privileges.  You can sit and chat with her about this and that later.  If you'll get out of the way, I have mages to call.  Hunters can be tricky sometimes.  Just be glad you're over here.  You haven't been caught yet and I'm not about to let that happen.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth leaps skyward and flies to a higher spot far from the two smaller dragons and gives a very loud scream that sends several more dragons streaking in to meet her.  As the two half-dragons watch the assembly Merenth issues orders to fly and they all rise from the cliffs in an intricate pattern of flapping wings before the whole group disappears, leaving only the queen, who glides back to her vacant spot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;What, you were too busy watching me to talk?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Yes.  It's always interesting to watch takeoff formations.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, knock it off you silly child.  It's far more interesting to watch Kaelia playing with the butterflies.  I think they like her.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Of course they do.  Why else would I play with them?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Then go play with them.  I want to sit in the sun for a while longer.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
With a little grin at his foster mother, Corathin turns back to Kyla.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Sorry. I get distracted easily.  Maybe it's because I spent too much time as a dragon.  I haven't been in human form for over a year now.  But flying can be addictive.  Especially when you don't have to keep wondering when you'll change back and plummet to your death.  If you can't learn to control it yourself, you need a feather-dragon to help.  They'll make sure you don't change at the wrong time.  How long ago did you find out you could change?  Maybe I can judge how long it'll be before you can control it.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
