Corathin looks briefly up at Merenth with an impish grin before he goes on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I was overconfident once I sorted out my extra set of limbs during my changes.  I always thought I could fly a little longer before I couldn't fly anymore so I stayed in the air as long as possible.  Once I almost <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>did</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> plummet to my death but I was close enough to the treetops to snag on a branch on the way down without breaking something.  I can never remember how I got <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>out</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of that tree, though.  I did feel the change coming on but I ignored it because it felt so <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>good</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to fly.  So I kept going and I even climbed higher but then I lost the use of my wings and I just dropped.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>That</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> was the worst experience of my life for a while.  It was the only thing that kept me from overdoing it again.  The only thing that was worse was trying to cringe into the base of a cliff when I had a small group of hungry dragons advancing on me!&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;And one thing worse than <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>that</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> would have been if I'd spotted you any later when you could've been between their teeth.  And by the way, I would like you to meet Iris as well, if you'd wait around, Corathin.  Didn't you tell me once that you liked green dragons more than any other besides me?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Green? I...umm...well, they seem to have more of a likable personality than some others, I suppose...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Merenth takes a brief glance at the two half-dragons before pointing her nose to the sky, howling with laughter.  Corathin hides his head under a wing in embarassment.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Hah!  I caught you off-guard again!  And in front of a lady, too!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;Hey!  Kitrin is male!  He's a friend and posted in the Oven.  And I'm just the little messenger!&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Who tries to seduce about every female green he sees.  I won't have any of that when you meet Iris!  And don't say I didn't warn you!&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Corathin glares &quot;angrily&quot; at Merenth.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->!  And didn't you say we could talk about other stuff <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>later</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->?  We were supposed to be talking about half-dragons!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Then talk!  I'm just a cheerful distraction.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:skyblue;">&quot;I'd have to agree on that.  Well, Let's see... It took me how long?  Three years, I think.  And that was with Kaelia to help for the last three months.  So about another half year at most if our good queen Merenth would let us borrow her pet.  Depending on a number of factors.&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
